ultad de Biología, Universidad de La Habana, Cuba.\n            \n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n\n      \n    \n  \n\n\n          \n        \n        \n  \n    \n      \n        \n          \n  \n    \n      PMID:\n    \n  \n\n  \n    20562011\n  \n\n  \n\n\n        \n      \n        \n          \n  \n    \n      DOI:\n    \n  \n\n  \n    \n      10.1016/j.biochi.2010.05.007\n    \n  \n\n  \n\n\n        \n      \n    \n  \n\n\n        \n  Free article\n\n        \n  Item in Clipboard\n\n      \n      \n        \n\n        \n\n\n  \n    \n    \n    \n    \n      \n  Enzymatic and structural characterization of a basic phospholipase A(2) from the sea anemone Condylactis gigantea\n\n\n    \n  \n\n\n        \n\n        \n\n\n  \n    \n      \n        Lazara Romero&nbsp;et al.\n      \n    \n  \n  \n    \n      \n        Biochimie.\n      \n      \n        \n          2010 Aug.\n        \n      \n    \n  \n\n\n        \n  Free article\n\n        \n          \n            Show details\n          \n          \n            \n\n\n  \n    Display options\n  \n\n  \n    \n      Display options\n    \n\n    \n      \n        \n          \n            Format\n          \n          \n  Abstract\n\n  PubMed\n\n  PMID\n\n\n        \n      \n    \n  \n\n          \n        \n        \n          \n            \n              \n  \n    \n      \n\n      Biochimie\n    Actions\n              Search in PubMed\n            \n              Search in NLM Catalog\n            \n              Add to Search\n            . 2010 Aug;92(8):1063-71.\n\n    \n  \n  \n    \n      \n        doi: 10.1016/j.biochi.2010.05.007.\n      \n    \n    \n    \n      \n        Epub 2010 May 26.\n      \n    \n  \n\n\n            \n          \n\n          \n          \n          \n            \n\n\n  \n    \n      \n        \n          \n            Authors\n          \n          \n\n\n  \n    Lazara Romero&nbsp;\n                1\n              ,&nbsp;Silvana Marcussi,&nbsp;Daniela P Marchi-Salvador,&nbsp;Floriano P Silva Jr,&nbsp;André L Fuly,&nbsp;Rodrigo G Stábeli,&nbsp;Saulo L da Silva,&nbsp;Jorge González,&nbsp;Alberto Del Monte,&nbsp;Andreimar M Soares\n  \n\n\n        \n      \n\n      \n\n      \n\n      \n\n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            Affiliation\n          \n          \n            \n              1 Centro de Estudios de Proteínas, Facultad de Biología, Universidad de La Habana, Cuba.\n            \n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n\n      \n    \n  \n\n\n          \n          \n  \n    \n      \n        \n          \n  \n    \n      PMID:\n    \n  \n\n  \n    20562011\n  \n\n  \n\n\n        \n      \n        \n          \n  \n    \n      DOI:\n    \n  \n\n  \n    \n      10.1016/j.biochi.2010.05.007\n    \n  \n\n  \n\n\n        \n      \n    \n  \n\n\n          \n  Item in Clipboard\n\n        \n      \n    \n  \n\n\n  \n\n\n          Full text links\n        CiteDisplay options\n      Display options\n    \n            Format\n          AbstractPubMedPMID\n\n  \n\n  \n\n\n\n  \n    \n      \n        Abstract\n        \n      \n      \n        \n          \n            \n              \n                \n\n\n  \n    \n      \n      This work aimed at the isolation and structural/functional characterization of a phospholipase A(2) (CgPLA(2)) from the extract of the anemone Condylactis gigantea. CgPLA(2) was isolated with a high purity level through three chromatographic steps, showing pI 8.6 and molecular weights of 14,500 and 29,000 for the monomer and dimer, respectively. CgPLA(2) showed a high catalytic activity upon fluorescent phospholipids inducing no direct hemolytic activity. This enzyme, which is Ca(2+)-dependent, showed a lower stability against temperature and pH variations when compared with snake venom enzymes. The enzymatic activity was significantly reduced or completely abolished after chemical modification of CgPLA(2) with BPB. Its cDNA was then obtained, with 357 base pairs which codified for a mature protein of 119 amino acid residues. A comparative analysis of the primary structure of CgPLA(2) revealed 84%, 61%, 43% and 42% similarity to the PLA(2)s from Adamsia carciniopados, Nematostella vectensis, Vipera russelli russelli and Bothrops jararacussu, respectively.\n    \n  \n\n  \n\n\n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n    \n\n    \n\n    \n\n  \n\n\n  \n  \n\n\n  \n    Copyright  2010 Elsevier Masson SAS. All rights reserved.\n  \n\n\n  \n  PubMed Disclaimer\n\n  \n\n  \n  \n\n  \n\n  \n  \n  \n  \n    \n      \n        Publication types\n      \n\n      \n      Research Support, Non-U.S. Gov&#x27;t\n    Actions\n              Search in PubMed\n            \n                Search in MeSH\n              \n              Add to Search\n            \n    \n  \n\n\n  \n  \n    \n      \n        MeSH terms\n      \n\n      \n      Amino Acid Sequence\n    Actions\n              Search in PubMed\n            \n                Search in MeSH\n              \n              Add to Search\n            \n      Animals\n    Actions\n              Search in PubMed\n            \n                Search in MeSH\n              \n              Add to Search\n            \n      Base Sequence\n    Actions\n              Search in PubMed\n            \n                Search in MeSH\n              \n              Add to Search\n            \n      Chromatography, Liquid\n    Actions\n              Search in PubMed\n            \n                Search in MeSH\n              \n              Add to Search\n            \n      DNA, Complementary\n    Actions\n              Search in PubMed\n            \n                Search in MeSH\n              \n              Add to Search\n            \n      Electrophoresis, Polyacrylamide Gel\n    Actions\n              Search in PubMed\n            \n                Search in MeSH\n              \n              Add to Search\n            \n      Hemolysis\n    Actions\n              Search in PubMed\n  